    "reasoning": "(a) **Time left until resolution**\nToday is June 28, 2026. The deadline is July 1, 2026. There are approximately 3 days remaining until resolution.\n\n(b) **Status quo outcome if nothing changes**\nIf no S-1 has been filed by now (June 28), and nothing changes in the next 3 days, the question resolves NO. The window is essentially closed \u2014 an S-1 filing in the next 3 business days would be extraordinary given the lack of any reported imminent filing.\n\n(c) **Scenario for NO outcome**\nAnthropic has not filed an S-1 by June 28. With only 3 days left, the practical window is essentially shut. The company may be continuing to raise private capital (the $350B valuation round with Microsoft and Nvidia), the IPO market may have cooled, or Anthropic may have decided to delay until 2027 or later. No public reports as of the question's refresh indicate an imminent S-1 filing.\n\n(d) **Scenario for YES outcome**\nAnthropic would need to file an S-1 with the SEC in the next 3 days (by June 30, 2026). This is extremely unlikely unless there had been significant pre-filing preparation that simply wasn't publicly reported, and even then S-1 filings are typically preceded by weeks of public signals. There is no indication in the background material that this was imminent.\n\n(e) **Base rate**\nNo reliable base rate available \u2014 proceeding on priors. Generally, large tech IPO S-1 filings are well-telegraphed events with significant lead time. The background from December 2025 described \"early talks\" and engagement with a law firm, which typically precedes an actual S-1 filing by many months. The original forecast of 28% reflected the uncertainty at the time.\n\n(f) **How current data/news moves me from base rate**\nThe question was refreshed today, June 28, 2026 \u2014 just 3 days before the deadline. The fact that this is being refreshed now, combined with the lack of any background update indicating a filing has occurred or is imminent, strongly suggests the filing has NOT happened. If an S-1 had been filed, that would be major news and would likely be referenced in the background. The absence of such information, combined with the extremely narrow time window remaining, pushes the probability very close to zero.\n\n(g) **How my view has changed since the original forecast**\nThe original forecast of 28% was made when there was roughly 6+ months remaining and Anthropic was described as being in \"early talks.\" Now, with 3 days left and no indication of a filing, the probability has collapsed dramatically. The passage of time without a filing is strong evidence against YES resolution.\n\n(h) **Community prediction divergence**\nThe prior forecast was 28%. Given the 3-day window remaining and no evidence of a filed S-1, the current probability should be near 1-3%. If the community has updated significantly downward (which triggered this refresh), I agree with that direction. Any remaining probability above ~2% reflects only the tiny chance of a surprise same-week filing that somehow wasn't anticipated in the background material.\n\n**Summary:** With only 3 days until the July 1, 2026 deadline, and no indication in the provided background that an S-1 has been filed or is imminent, this question is almost certain to resolve NO. The 28% prior was appropriate in December 2025 but is now obsolete given the passage of time without a filing.\n\nProbability: 3%",
